---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Playbooks — Kenius" description="Six industry playbooks from a boutique AI consultancy: for property management, real estate, law, accounting, home services and freight — the pain we see, what we’d build, and what changes." path="/work">
    <section class="page-hero">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="breadcrumb reveal"><a href="/">Kenius</a> — Playbooks</div>
        <h1 class="reveal" data-d="1">Playbooks: where AI <span class="it mark">pays for itself.</span></h1>
        <p class="lead reveal" data-d="2">We go deep in a handful of industries where AI quietly pays for itself. For each: the work that’s bleeding time, what we’d build, and what changes once it’s live.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" style="padding-top:0" id="property">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="detail reveal">
          <div><div class="d-num">/01</div><div class="cap" style="margin-top:1rem">Property management</div></div>
          <div>
            <p class="ledger-line"><time>02:14</time><span class="msg">“no heat — unit 4B”</span><span class="st">triaged emergency · dispatched</span></p>
            <h2>Every tenant handled — even the 11pm “no heat” call.</h2>
            <p class="d-lead">Tenants don’t message during office hours. Maintenance requests, lease questions and vendor chasing pile up overnight — and the real emergencies hide among the routine.</p>
            <ul class="checks">
              <li><span>AI leasing assistant &amp; 24/7 tenant support</span></li>
              <li><span>Maintenance triage — routine vs. emergency</span></li>
              <li><span>Vendor coordination &amp; dispatch</span></li>
            </ul>
            <p class="cap" style="margin-top:1.4rem;color:var(--muted)">Outcome — auto-handles the bulk of inbound, escalates real emergencies in seconds. <span style="text-transform:none;letter-spacing:0">(illustrative)</span></p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="detail reveal" id="real-estate">
          <div><div class="d-num">/02</div><div class="cap" style="margin-top:1rem">Real estate</div></div>
          <div>
            <p class="ledger-line"><time>18:22</time><span class="msg">portal lead · 3BR, pre-approved</span><span class="st">qualified · tour booked</span></p>
            <h2>Reply to every new lead in 30 seconds — not three hours.</h2>
            <p class="d-lead">Speed-to-lead wins deals, but agents are out showing homes while portal leads go cold. The follow-up that does happen is inconsistent.</p>
            <ul class="checks">
              <li><span>Lead-qualification agent (budget, timeline, pre-approval)</span></li>
              <li><span>SMS &amp; email follow-up that books showings</span></li>
              <li><span>Listing Q&amp;A assistant</span></li>
            </ul>
            <p class="cap" style="margin-top:1.4rem;color:var(--muted)">Outcome — sub-minute first response; showings booked to the right agent. <span style="text-transform:none;letter-spacing:0">(illustrative)</span></p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="detail reveal" id="law">
          <div><div class="d-num">/03</div><div class="cap" style="margin-top:1rem">Law firms</div></div>
          <div>
            <p class="ledger-line"><time>03:51</time><span class="msg">after-hours injury call</span><span class="st">conflict-checked · consult booked</span></p>
            <h2>Capture the after-hours inquiry — book only the cases worth your time.</h2>
            <p class="d-lead">Most legal inquiries arrive after hours and go to whoever replies first. Meanwhile attorneys lose hours to intake and document chasing.</p>
            <ul class="checks">
              <li><span>24/7 intake &amp; case qualification (jurisdiction, conflicts)</span></li>
              <li><span>Document collection workflows</span></li>
              <li><span>Fees &amp; process FAQ</span></li>
            </ul>
            <p class="cap" style="margin-top:1.4rem;color:var(--muted)">Outcome — qualified, booked consults; the rest politely declined. <span style="text-transform:none;letter-spacing:0">(illustrative)</span></p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="detail reveal" id="accounting">
          <div><div class="d-num">/04</div><div class="cap" style="margin-top:1rem">Accounting &amp; CPA</div></div>
          <div>
            <p class="ledger-line"><time>06:39</time><span class="msg">“still need my W-2?”</span><span class="st">docs collected</span></p>
            <h2>Tax-season document chasing — handled, without one more reminder.</h2>
            <p class="d-lead">Onboarding and the endless “still waiting on your W-2” chase eat your busiest weeks. Clients mean well; they just need a nudge.</p>
            <ul class="checks">
              <li><span>Client onboarding &amp; document-chase agents</span></li>
              <li><span>Scheduling &amp; deadline reminders</span></li>
              <li><span>Internal knowledge bot for staff</span></li>
            </ul>
            <p class="cap" style="margin-top:1.4rem;color:var(--muted)">Outcome — collection runs itself; files land ready to prep. <span style="text-transform:none;letter-spacing:0">(illustrative)</span></p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="detail reveal" id="home-services">
          <div><div class="d-num">/05</div><div class="cap" style="margin-top:1rem">Home services &amp; trades</div></div>
          <div>
            <p class="ledger-line"><time>23:58</time><span class="msg">missed call · furnace out</span><span class="st">called back · tech en route</span></p>
            <h2>Stop sending jobs to voicemail. Answer every call, book it, done.</h2>
            <p class="d-lead">For HVAC, plumbing and roofing, a missed call is a lost job — and they ring in while you’re on a roof. After-hours calls go straight to a competitor.</p>
            <ul class="checks">
              <li><span>24/7 voice agent that books the job</span></li>
              <li><span>Dispatch, confirmations &amp; reminders</span></li>
              <li><span>Quote follow-up</span></li>
            </ul>
            <p class="cap" style="margin-top:1.4rem;color:var(--muted)">Outcome — every call answered; emergencies routed to the on-call tech. <span style="text-transform:none;letter-spacing:0">(illustrative)</span></p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="detail reveal" id="freight">
          <div><div class="d-num">/06</div><div class="cap" style="margin-top:1rem">Freight &amp; logistics</div></div>
          <div>
            <p class="ledger-line"><time>04:12</time><span class="msg">“where’s my load #LT-4471?”</span><span class="st">ETA sent</span></p>
            <h2>Handle every “where’s my load?” — so dispatch can actually dispatch.</h2>
            <p class="d-lead">Brokers and carriers lose the day to status calls, carrier check-ins and appointment-setting — while the real exceptions, a detained truck or a missed pickup, hide in the noise.</p>
            <ul class="checks">
              <li><span>24/7 track-and-trace &amp; shipment-status agent</span></li>
              <li><span>Carrier check-in calls &amp; appointment scheduling</span></li>
              <li><span>Detention, POD chasing &amp; exception flagging</span></li>
            </ul>
            <p class="cap" style="margin-top:1.4rem;color:var(--muted)">Outcome — routine status calls handled; dispatch hears only the real exceptions. <span style="text-transform:none;letter-spacing:0">(illustrative)</span></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section dark">
      <div class="wrap">
        <span class="cap reveal">Not listed?</span>
        <p class="big-statement reveal" data-d="1" style="margin-top:1.4rem">Same playbook, <span class="it">your industry.</span></p>
        <p class="reveal" data-d="1" style="margin-top:1.6rem;color:var(--dark-muted);max-width:46ch">The pattern — answer, qualify, book, chase, log — repeats almost everywhere: clinics, restaurants, e-commerce, salons &amp; fitness, auto, insurance, recruiting. If your team repeats it every day, there’s an agent for it.</p>
        <p class="reveal" data-d="2" style="margin-top:2.2rem"><a class="tlink" href="/contact" style="color:var(--dark-text)">Tell us your one annoying task <span class="ar" aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a></p>
      </div>
    </section>
</Layout>
